Hi! I'm trying to get all the tickets from a particular view, here is part of my code:

    def get(self, view_id):
		creds['token'] = users[auth.username()]
		zenpy_client = Zenpy(**creds)
		tickets = zenpy_client.views.tickets(int(view_id))
		payload = {
			"tickets" : []
		}
		for ticket in tickets:
			aux = {"id": ticket.id,"subject": ticket.subject}
			payload["tickets"].append(aux)
		return payload

And the problem is, that single view got 103 tickets, but zenpy_client.views.tickets(int(view_id)), only gave me exactly 100 (It got sense because in Zendesk Api Core, there's a maximum of 100 tickets by Get a list of tickets).

Who I can get all the tickets?

